mpute every future position exactly)\nGate A at (1,4): open exactly when (t mod 2) is in {1}. So it is open at t=1,3,... and closed at t=0,2,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGate B at (5,3): open exactly when (t mod 2) is in {1}. So it is open at t=1,3,... and closed at t=0,2,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGuard P: walks a fixed cycle of length 4. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 4) as follows: t mod 4=0: (5,9); t mod 4=1: (4,9); t mod 4=2: (3,9); t mod 4=3: (4,9). This repeats forever.\nGuard Q: walks a fixed cycle of length 4. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 4) as follows: t mod 4=0: (7,5); t mod 4=1: (6,5); t mod 4=2: (6,6); t mod 4=3: (6,5). This repeats forever.\n\nYOUR JOB\nParcel 1: pick it up at (1,9) (map glyph '1'), deliver it to (8,6) (map glyph 'x'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nParcel 2: pick it up at (1,8) (map glyph '2'), deliver it to (3,7) (map glyph 'y'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nDeliver every parcel within 45 ticks. You move by committing to plans of\nexactly 5 moves at a time; you have at most 9 plans in total.\nIf you deliver the last parcel mid-plan, the game ends immediately and the unused\nmoves are discarded.\n\nWORKED EXAMPLE (for the rules only - this is NOT the map above): suppose you stand at\n(2,2), gate G at (3,2) has period 2 and is open when (t mod 2) = 1, and it is now t=0.\nMoving E now (arriving at t=1, when the gate is open) succeeds. But moving E at t=1\n(arriving at t=2, when the gate is closed) is a BUMP: you stay at (2,2) and tick 2 is\nwasted. The right play at t=1 is to WAIT once and then move E, arriving at t=3 when\nthe gate is open again.\n\nAfter each plan you receive only a per-tick log of OK/BUMP/CAUGHT/PICKED UP/DELIVERED. You are NEVER told where you are or why you bumped - track your position yourself.\n\nRESPOND IN EXACTLY THIS FORMAT (and put nothing after the PLAN line):\nTHOUGHTS: <your reasoning - any length; the referee ignores this>\nPOSITION: (x,y)\nPLAN: <exactly 5 moves from {N, S, E, W, WAIT}, separated by spaces>\n\nThe POSITION line must state the cell you predict you will occupy AFTER your plan has\nexecuted. The referee records your prediction but will never confirm or correct it.\n\nGive your first response now.\n",
